# Advanced Student Management System

An academic web application built using **Flask (Python)** and **MySQL** to manage student records, attendance, and marks through a simple web interface.

## Features
- Add, view, and delete student records
- Attendance management (Present / Absent)
- Marks management (subject-wise)
- View attendance and marks history
- Search students by name
- Filter students by branch and semester
- Clean UI using HTML, CSS, and Jinja templates

## Technologies Used
Python (Flask), MySQL, HTML, CSS, Jinja2, VS Code, GitHub

## Project Structure
Advanced_Student_Management_System/
- app.py  
- static/style.css  
- templates/index.html  
- templates/attendance.html  
- templates/marks.html  
- templates/view_attendance.html  
- templates/view_marks.html  
- database.sql  
- requirements.txt  

## How to Run
1. Clone repository  
   `git clone https://github.com/your-username/Advanced_Student_Management_System.git`

2. Create virtual environment  
   `python3 -m venv venv`  
   `source venv/bin/activate`

3. Install dependencies  
   `pip install -r requirements.txt`

4. Setup MySQL database  
   `mysql -u root -p`  
   `SOURCE database.sql;`

5. Update MySQL credentials in `app.py`

6. Run application  
   `python app.py`

7. Open browser  
   `http://127.0.0.1:5000`

## Purpose
This project is developed for academic use to demonstrate Flask backend development, MySQL database integration, CRUD operations, and server-side rendering using Jinja templates.

